# Files Shopify CLI (`theme dev` / `theme push`) must NEVER sync to the store.
# Note: the CLI already only uploads the 8 recognised theme dirs (assets, blocks,
# config, layout, locales, sections, snippets, templates). These rules make the
# intent explicit and add belt-and-suspenders coverage.

# ── Atomic-write temp files ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editors & Claude Code save as "<name>.tmp.<pid>.<hash>" then rename; the
# watcher can catch the temp file mid-write and error on illegal characters.
*.tmp.*
*/*.tmp.*

# ── Editor swap / backup files ───────────────────────────────────────────
*~
*.swp
*.bak

# ── Documentation — repo-only, never part of the live theme ──────────────
*.md
docs/
